org.vadere.util.geometry

Class LinkedCellsGrid<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.vadere.util.geometry.LinkedCellsGrid<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>

    public class LinkedCellsGrid<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<T>
    A grid augmenting the position of generic objects, for faster access. O(1) instead of O(n) for one fixed radius check. See LinkedCellsGrid#getObjects(java.awt.geometry.shapes.VPoint, double).

    • Constructor Detail

      • LinkedCellsGrid

        public LinkedCellsGrid(double left,
                       double top,
                       double width,
                       double height,
                       double sideLength)
        Generates a LinkedCellsGrid with given dimension, position and number of items on one side.
        Parameters:
        left - x-position of top left corner
        top - y-position of top left corner
        width - width of the grid, in world units (e.g. [m])
        height - height of the grid, in world units (e.g. [m])
        sideLength - number of items on one side. the total number of grid cells equals sideLength^2

    • Method Detail

      • addObject

        public void addObject(T object,
                      VPoint pos)
        Adds a given object to the grid at the given position. The position is discretized automatically to fit in the cells.
        Parameters:
        object - object to add
        pos - position in the grid

      • getObjects

        public java.util.List<T> getObjects(VPoint pos,
                                    double radius)
        Returns a set of objects in the ball around pos with given radius.
        Parameters:
        pos - position of the center of the ball
        radius - radius of the ball
        Returns:
        set of objects, or an empty set if no objects are present.

      • removeObject

        public void removeObject(T object)
        Removes the objects equal to the given object from the grid regardless of their position. Note that this function has complexity O(N), with N = number of objects in the grid.

        Removes all objects.

        public boolean contains(T element)
